Challenges Faced
CIDR Planning

One challenge was ensuring that the private subnet used a unique CIDR range that did not overlap with the public subnet.

Subnet overlap prevents AWS from routing traffic correctly and results in deployment failures.


Understanding Route Tables

Initially it seemed that creating a private subnet automatically isolated it.

I learned that subnet privacy is determined by routing rather than by the subnet itself.

Without a route to an Internet Gateway, resources remain private.

Lessons Learned
Private subnets improve security through network isolation.
Route Tables determine internet accessibility.
Network ACLs provide subnet-level protection.
CIDR planning is essential for scalable network design.
Security is achieved through multiple layers rather than a single configuration.
